file=Cybersecurity/warden/custom/third-party-risk/assets/vendor-assessment-template.md · vsa:Vendor Security Assessment — [vendor] — [date]=> Assess proportionate to data + access. Feeds warden's risk-register. Critical = touches crown-jewel data (veil classification).\n · s:Scope=- Data touched: [class per veil — none / internal / confidential / PII / regulated]\n- Access: [systems/scope] \· Business function: [what we use them for]\n- Critical vendor: [y/n] \· Concentration/single-point-of-failure: [y/n]\n · p:Posture=- Certifications: [SOC 2 (scope/exceptions) \· ISO 27001 \· none → questionnaire]\n- Security questionnaire: [key answers / gaps]\n- Breach history: [known incidents]\n- Sub-processors: [who else touches our data downstream]\n · c(c:Contract (the controls)=- [ ] Data-processing agreement (DPA) in place\n- [ ] Breach-notification clause (they notify us within ___ )\n- [ ] Security requirements specified\n- [ ] Right-to-audit / evidence\n- [ ] Data return/deletion on exit\n · o:Outcome=- Risk score → register [R-ref] \· Treatment: [adopt / adopt-with-controls / reject]\n- Re-assessment cadence: [config]\n- On vendor breach → cortex IR + veil breach-notification review\n